  "prompt": "What are some of the best Soft Rock songs of all time?",
  "response": "Soft rock is a genre that blends elements of rock with softer melodies and often introspective lyrics. Here are some of the best soft rock songs of all time:\n\n1. **\"California Dreamin'\" - The Mamas & The Papas** (1965)\n2. **\"Baker Street\" - Gerry Rafferty** (1978)\n3. **\"Hotel California\" - Eagles** (1976)\n4. **\"Just the Way You Are\" - Billy Joel** (1977)\n5. **\"Wonderful Tonight\" - Eric Clapton** (1976)\n6. **\"You Are So Beautiful\" - Joe Cocker** (1974)\n7. **\"Your Song\" - Elton John** (1970)\n8. **\"Bridge Over Troubled Water\" - Simon & Garfunkel** (1970)\n9. **\"I Will Always Love You\" - Dolly Parton** (1973)\n10. **\"Take It Easy\" - Eagles** (1972)\n11. **\"Lean on Me\" - Bill Withers** (1972)\n12. **\"Dust in the Wind\" - Kansas** (1977)\n13. **\"The Way It Is\" - Bruce Hornsby and the Range** (1986)\n14. **\"Goodbye Yellow Brick Road\" - Elton John** (1973)\n15. **\"I Want to Know What Love Is\" - Foreigner** (1984)\n\nThese songs not only showcase the essence of soft rock but have also left a lasting impact on music and culture. Whether through their lyrics or melodies, they continue to resonate with audiences today.",
